\f0\fs24 \cf0 The morning sun cast long shadows across the cobblestone streets as Maria opened the door to her small bookshop. She had inherited it from her grandmother, who had run it for nearly fifty years before her. The smell of old paper and leather bindings greeted her like an old friend.\
\
